=Create Chrome OS Recovery Drive= 
----

==Create a Chrome OS recovery drive== 
* ====Obtain a USB drive or SD card [[@http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B007JR531I/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B007JR531I&linkCode=as2&tag=mcdotechserv-20|at least 4GB in size]]==== 
* ====In Chrome OS, simply insert the drive in the computer, go to [[@chrome://imageburner/]] and follow the prompts==== 
* ====In Windows, Mac OS X or Linux, follow the instructions provided by Google [[http://support.google.com/chromeos/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=1080595|available here]]==== 
==== ==== 
==Reinstall Chrome OS== 
# ====Start your computer.==== 
# ====When the "Chrome OS is missing or damaged" screen appears, insert the USB flash drive or SD card you created==== 
# ====Wait for the Chromebook to boot from the recovery drive==== 
# ====Follow the instructions that appear on the screen==== 
# ====On successful installation of the Chrome OS, the computer will automatically restart==== 
# ====Remove the recovery drive from the computer==== 

Source: [[http://www.google.com/support/chromeos/bin/answer.py?answer=1046510]]


